-- Pfizer and Sanofi decline comment on stake talk
-- 
-- Mon Oct 8, 2007 11:39am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/08/us-sanofiaventis-shares-pfizer-idUSL0829036920071008

 

 LONDON/NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Officials at French drugmaker Sanofi-Aventis ( SASY.PA ) and Pfizer ( PFE.N ) declined to comment on Monday on market talk Pfizer was looking to buy stakes from Sanofi's major shareholders. 

 "We don't comment on rumors or market speculation," a spokesman for Pfizer in New York said. "We've nothing to say -- we don't comment on market rumors," a Sanofi spokesman said. Oil company Total ( TOTF.PA ) and cosmetics firm L'Oreal ( OREP.PA ), which jointly own about 23 percent of Sanofi's share capital, have previously made it clear they do not consider their stakes strategic. L'Oreal and Total were not immediately available to comment.